Download Photo
Liam Butterworth
Senior Vice President and President, Powertrain Systems and Delphi Product & Service Solutions
Liam Butterworth is senior vice president of Delphi and president, Delphi Powertrain Systems (PT), a position he has held since February 2014. Prior to this role, he served as vice president of Delphi Electrical/Electronic Architecture (E/EA) and president of Delphi Connection Systems (DCS) since October 2012.

Based in Bascharage, Luxembourg, Mr. Butterworth joined Delphi in 2012 after the company acquired FCI Motorized Vehicles Division (MVL), a company where he had been president and general manager.

He joined FCI in 2000 and over the next 12 years held several positions in sales, marketing, purchasing and general management. Liam previously worked for Lucas Industries and TRW Automotive in the United Kingdom.

He is fluent in French and English and holds an MBA from Lancaster University in England.
​

























   


 









